<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-12-1089 </DOCNO><TEXT>Using mock coal samples (fibre boards, Al or Cu foils, distance pieces)the dependence of the scatter-transmission count rate on thickness, 'ash'content, density and sample inhomogeneities relating to composition anddensity was studied. It is shown that inhomogeneities which might occurat a conveyor belt would have a much smaller effect on the count ratecompared to possible thickness variations.</TEXT></DOC>